                  <handDesc>
                     <p>The writing, which is apparently all in one hand, indicates that the accountant copied several days' worth of items in one sitting because at certain points, abrupt changes appear, such as difference in the ink and the freshness or bluntness of the reed pen, and such circumstances of writing as posture, haste, etc., would occasion.  (Goodspeed 1902, 31)</p>
